title: Ulster get bonus in victory over Blues
text:
Ulster get bonus in victory over Blues 
Irish Examiner Saturday 24th October, 2015 
Ulster 24 Cardiff Blues 17Ulster racked up a third win from five Guinness PRO12 games as they claimed a bonus point 24-17 victory over the Cardiff Blues.Tries from Andrew Trimble, Paul Marshall, Stuart McCloskey and man of the match Nick Williams paved the way for the victory, which takes their unbeaten league record at home to 14 games.It was also their third bonus point win - all have been secured at the Kingspan Stadium - which was much-needed after having lost their only two games away from Belfast....
